 In the most simple case, a spec will have an buildsystem declaration such
 as `BuildSystem: cmake` and no manually specified build scripts at all.
+Declaring a build system automatically adds
+`BuildRequires: rpm-build(cmake)` so the package that ships the
+corresponding macros can be installed before the build (mock and similar
+tools will pull it in on a clean builder). Packages that provide
+buildsystem macros should therefore also
+`Provides: rpm-build(<name>)`.
+
 However it's common to have to manually tweak a thing or two. There are
 several ways how to accomplish this, what's appropriate depends on the
 case.
